The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 28 September is 377,035 (669.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 September, there were 32,402 new confirmed cases (57.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 September, there were 20,295 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 60% (12107 extra cases).
